{"questionId": "a7146625-47ea-49cb-9061-578e226240d5_9", "correctAnswer": "9", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Cancel the common factor", "content": "Since $k > -6$, $(k+6) \\ne 0$, so:<br/><br/>$$\\frac{27(k+6)}{3(k+6)} = \\frac{27}{3} = 9$$"}, {"title": "Identify $c$", "content": "The expression equals the constant $c = 9$.<br/><br/>The answer is <strong>9</strong>."}]}